I've been wanting an M1A for decades, but too broke (wife's a teacher, and I'm a substitute teacher & DV to boot). I'm hoping that in cleaning out my crowded house, someone will find stuff they'd like in trade for an M1A or a Ruger SR762 and a bit more.

On offer is:

* 6 pieces of diner furniture from a closed diner in Ada...several benches, and a semi-circular piece that holds about 5-6. All are thick pine/oak and heavy-duty, covered in thick green Naugahyde;

* A MacBook G4 laptop (running OSX, missing electric cord);

* A Pioneer SR-9 Reverberation Amplifier and several audiophile-grade sets of home/bookshelf speakers;

* A Jazzy 'bariatric' electric mobility chair. Holds up to 500lbs, looks a bit rough, but works perfectly;

* (If you know an electronics repair person) An ADC Sound Shaper Two MKll equalizer for home hi-end audio. One channel is out...;

* A single 32-band, 1-channel pro-grade EQ (I have no hookups to check it out, but got it 'in good condition' from OU);

* A 300-700 WPC home-theatre/DJ amp. Stable down to 1 ohm, dual-monoblock construction, fan-cooled. Model QSC CX6T;

* A FULL Canon A-1 35mm camera rig. Has 3 lenses, 2 on-off camera flashes, 2 'slave' flashes, filters, hard carrying case, tripod, misc. other accessories. Has single black-colored body I've kept clean and lubed all these years, and professionally maintained, to boot. The flash units/filters/tripod, etc alone are still usable and well worth over $850...

* A pair of fairly rare Pioneer HPM-100 (200w models) speakers - one missing a woofer (blown), both need refinishing and new grilles, but sound great otherwise;

* If it'll help get me either rifle (and hopefully a Phase Linear PL4000 MKl preamp as well), I'll be happy to add in both my Carver C-1 preamp (needs recapping) and my MacIntosh MC2205 power amp (works, but needs new faceplate).

*Finally, if I have to, I'll throw in a 1969 Gilbarco gas pump. Only needs glass pieces. VGC.

Here's the deal: I need to get rid of stuff to make room to turn around, and I'd rather it went for a reason. I'll trade some combination of the stuff above for the rifle I want  Heck, a Springfield M1A or the Ruger SR762 and an SKS would get the whole 'shooting match', as an honest -if general and slightly low- valuation is approximately $5,000.00 +/- !

Given my disabilities, you'd need to come here with both a trailer and several extra healthy backs to load up all this stuff. Trust me, you'll be doing us BOTH a favor, and make a long-held dream for me come true.
